'''Ion Dezideriu Sîrbu''' (also known as '''Ion Desideriu Sârbu''' or '''I. D. Sîrbu'''; June 28, 1919 &ndash; September 17, 1989) was a Romanian philosopher, novelist, essayist and dramatist.
Sîrbu was born in [[Petrila]], Hunedoara. A university associate professor and theater critic, he was a victim of the [[Communist Romania|communist regime]], spending about 6 years (1957-1963) as a [[political prisoner]]. He died at [[Craiova]], aged 70. His main novel, ''Adio, Europa!'' ("Goodbye, Europe!"), was published posthumously.
