'''Romanas Plečkaitis''' (August 11, 1933 – August 17, 2009, [[Vilnius]], [[Lithuania]]) - [[Lithuanians|Lithuanian]] philosopher, logic, philosophy, history researcher, Doctor habil, Professor. Romanas Plečkaitis translated the main [[Immanuel Kant]] works into [[Lithuanian language]], wrote the history of Lithuanian philosophy and logic issues, published over 300 publications in various academic, has developed 27 PhDs.
